  "prompt": "How can I boil chicken?",
  "response": "Here's a simple method to boil chicken:\n\n1. Preparation:\n- Choose boneless or bone-in chicken pieces\n- Place chicken in a pot\n- Add enough water or broth to cover the chicken completely\n\n2. Boiling process:\n- Bring water to a boil over high heat\n- Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low\n- Let chicken simmer gently\n\n3. Cooking times:\n- Boneless chicken breasts: 12-15 minutes\n- Bone-in chicken pieces: 25-30 minutes\n- Whole chicken: 1-1.5 hours\n\n4. Check doneness:\n- Use a meat thermometer to ensure internal temperature reaches 165\u00b0F (74\u00b0C)\n- Cut into thickest part of chicken to check for no pink color\n\n5. Optional additions:\n- Add salt, pepper, herbs, or garlic for flavor\n- Consider adding vegetables or aromatics to the water\n\n6. After cooking:\n- Remove chicken from pot\n- Let it rest for a few minutes\n- Slice or shred as desired\n\nTips:\n- Do not overcook to prevent dryness\n- Skim off any foam that forms on top during boiling",
